FORMAT: 1A

# 373swetarts
The Comics API is a **fantastic** way to retrieve information about **comics**, **characters**, and the **people** who helped create them!

# Group Characters
Information for the retrieval of characters

## Character Collection [/characters]
### List all Characters [GET]
+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [{ "id"   : 1,
           "name" : "Captain Obvious",
           "image": "imagepath"
        },
        {  "id"   : 2,
           "name" : "Discernable Woman",
           "image": "imagepath"
        }]


## Character [/characters/{id}]
A single **Character** object with all its details

+ Parameters
    + id (required, number, `1`) ... Numeric `id` of the Character to perform action with. Has example value.

### Retrieve a Character [GET]
+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Header

            X-My-Header: The Value

    + Body

            {  "id"         : 1,
            "name"       : "Captain Obvious",
            "alias"      : "Obvious Lee",
            "image"      : "image???",
            "description": "Well he's generally obvious",
            "gender"     : "male",
            "origin"     : "Obviousville, OB",
            "powers"     : [  "Stating the obvious",
                              "Obvious Ray",
                              "Obvlivion"
                           ],
            "teams"      : [  "Heroes of the Psyche"
                           ],
            "allies"     : [{ "id" : 2,
                              "name": "Discernable Woman"
                            }],
            "villans"    : [{ "id" : 3,
                              "name": "Double Entendre Dave"
                            }],
            "creators"    : [{ "id"  : 1,
                              "name": "Guy who lives with his mom"
                           },
                           { "id"  : 2,
                              "name": "The guy who lives with his mom's best friend"
                           }],
            "series"     : [{ "id"   : 1,
                              "title": "The Adventures of Captain Obvious"
                           }]
            }

# Group People
Information for retrieving infomation about people

## People Collection [/people]
### List all People [GET]
+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [{ "id"   : 1,
           "name" : "Guy who lives with his mom"
        },
        {  "id"   : 2,
           "name" : "The guy who lives with his mom's best friend"
        },
        {  "id"   : 3,
           "name" : "The collective internet"
        }]
        
## Person [/people/{id}]
A single **Person** object with all its details

+ Parameters
    + id (required, number, `1`) ... Numeric `id` of the Person to perform the action with. Has example value.

### Retrieve a Person [GET]
+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body
    
            { "id"        : 1,
              "name"      : "Guy who lives with his mom",
              "image"     : "imagepath",
              "birth_date": "566265600",
              "country"   : "USA",
              "job_title" : "Jobless",
              "website"   : "google.com",
              "gender"    : "male",
              "characters": [{ "id"  : 1,
                               "name": "Captain Obvious"
                            },
                            {  "id"  : 2,
                               "name": "Discernable Woman"
                            }],
              "series"    : [{ "id"   : 1,
                               "title": "The Adventures of Captain Obvious"
                            }]
            }

# Group Series
Information for retrieving **Comic Series**

## Series Collection [/series]
### List all Series [GET]
+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [{ "id"   : 1,
           "title": "The Adventures of Captain Obvious"
        },
        {  "id"   : 2,
           "title": "Obviously, or How I Saved The Planet from Myself"
        }]
        
## Series [/series/{id}]
A single **Series** object with all its details.

+ Parameters
    + id (required, number, `1`) ... Numeric `id` of the Series to perform the action with. Has example value.
    
### Retrieve a Series [GET]
+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body
    
            {  "id"         : 1,
               "title"      : "The Adventures of Captain Obvious",
               "image"      : "imagepath",
               "launch_date": "566265600",
               "publisher"  : "Just OK Studios",
               "characters" : [{ "id"  : 1,
                                 "name": "Captain Obvious"
                              },
                              {  "id"  : 2,
                                 "name": "Discernable Woman"
                              }],
               "people"     : [{ "id"  : 1,
                                 "name" : "Guy who lives with his mom"
                              },
                              { "id"   : 2,
                                "name": "The guy who lives with his mom's best friend"
                              }]
            }